                             int[] jCol,
                             double[] values)
        Evaluates the Jacobian matrix for the optimization problem.
        Specified by:
        eval_jac_g in class Ipopt
        Parameters:
        n - The number of decision variables.
        x - An array containing the current values of the decision variables.
        new_x - Indicates whether the values in the `x` array are new.
        m - The number of constraints.
        nele_jac - The number of non-zero elements in the Jacobian matrix.
        iRow - An array to store the row indices of the non-zero elements in the Jacobian matrix.
        jCol - An array to store the column indices of the non-zero elements in the Jacobian matrix.
        values - An array to store the values of the non-zero elements in the Jacobian matrix, or `null` to determine the structure of the matrix.
        Returns:
        `true` if the evaluation was successful, `false` otherwise.
